Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Category A: Cars (Number):

For cars registered with Certificates of Entitlement (COEs) obtained before Feb 2014 bidding exercises, Category A cars refer to cars up to 1,600cc and Category B cars refer to cars above 1,600cc.  For cars registered with COEs obtained from Feb 2014 1st bidding exercise onwards, Category A cars refer to cars up to 1,600cc and 97kW and Category B cars refer to cars above 1,600cc or 97kW.
Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Category B: Cars  (Number):

For cars registered with Certificates of Entitlement (COEs) obtained before Feb 2014 bidding exercises, Category A cars refer to cars up to 1,600cc and Category B cars refer to cars above 1,600cc.  For cars registered with COEs obtained from Feb 2014 1st bidding exercise onwards, Category A cars refer to cars up to 1,600cc and 97kW and Category B cars refer to cars above 1,600cc or 97kW.
Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Category C: Goods Vehicles & Buses - Category C: Goods Vehicles & Buses Not Under ETS (Number):

Refers to the Early Turnover Scheme (ETS).  Between 24 Apr 2013 and 30 Apr 2016, vehicle owners can de-register their existing diesel-propelled Category C vehicles that were registered before 1 Jan 2001 and register a replacement vehicle within 1 month of de-registration by paying a discounted Prevailing Quota Premium (PQP) under the ETS.  From 1 Aug 2015, the ETS was extended to existing diesel-propelled Category C vehicles that were registered between 1 Jan 2001 and 30 Sep 2006 and will be de-registered between 1 Aug 2015 and 31 Jul 2017.
Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Category C: Goods Vehicles & Buses - Category C: Goods Vehicles & Buses Under ETS (Number):

ETS refers to the Early Turnover Scheme.  Between 24 Apr 2013 and 31 Jul 2017, vehicle owners can de-register their existing diesel-propelled Category C vehicles that were registered before 1 Jan 2001 and register a replacement vehicle within 1 month of de-registration by paying a discounted Prevailing Quota Premium (PQP) under the ETS.  From 1 Aug 2015, the ETS was extended to existing diesel-propelled Category C vehicles that were registered between 1 Jan 2001 and 30 Sep 2006 and will be de-registered between 1 Aug 2015 and 31 Mar 2021.  From 1 April 2021 to 31 March 2023, vehicle owners can de-register their existing Euro 2/3/4 Category C diesel vehicles and register an eligible replacement vehicle within 1 month of deregistration by paying a discounted Prevailing Quota Premium under the enhanced ETS.
Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Taxis (Number):

Prior to Aug 2012, taxi operators can bid for a new Certificate of Entitlement (COE) or pay Prevailing Quota Premium (PQP) to register a taxi under Category A.  The latter is only in the case of a new taxi that replaces a deregistered one within 6 months.  From Aug 2012, all taxis pay for COEs based on the PQP of Category A.
Total New Motor Vehicles Registered - Vehicles Exempted From VQS (Number):

Includes vehicles which are exempted from the Vehicle Quota System (VQS), for example, scheduled and school buses, emergency vehicles, diplomatic vehicles, vehicles under the Disabled Person Scheme and vehicles for off-the-road use.
